    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Family Circle Joins Hormel in a Promotion</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Kim Foltz</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Family Circle magazine has joined forces with George A. Hormel &amp; Company, the processed foods company in Austin, Minn., to promote a special-edition Family Circle cookbook and to celebrate Hormel's 100th anniversary.</p>
        <p>Beginning in June, more than one million copies of the cookbook will be available in about 8,000 supermarkets. It will be given without charge to each shopper who buys three Hormel products at one time; others may buy it for $1.95.</p>
        <p>The cookbook will be distributed by Hormel and Time Distribution Services, a joint venture between The New York Times Company, which publishes Family Circle, and the Time Inc. Magazine Company.</p>
      </block>
